The paper deals with a specific type of cyber attack, namely combosquatting, which involves registering domains that combine a popular trademark with one or more phrases. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it involves analyzing and mitigating security threats. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of large-scale data sets, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the different types of abuse that combosquatting is used for, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) or software engineering (cs.SE).
